text: Eddumailaram is a census town in Sangareddy District of Telangana. == Demographics == As of the 2001 India census, Yeddumailaram had a population of 13,584. Males constitute 52% of the population and females, 48%. Yeddumailaram has an average literacy rate of 77%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 82%, and female literacy is 71%. In Yeddumailaram, 13% of the population is under 6 years of age. == References == Category:Census towns in Medak district
